To calculate the LIX (Läsfärdighetsindex, or Readability Index) score of the given text, we will follow the formula developed by Carl-Herman Nilsson in 1969. 

The LIX score is based on two variables: 

1. The average number of words per sentence (number of words in the text divided by the number of sentences).
2. The average percentage of complex words in the text (those with more than 6 letters or those with 3 syllables or more).

