   ('ser' does NOT have more than 6 letters)
9. lokaler 
   ('lokaler is not in text but 'lokal' is)
10. kontrollera
   (yes 'kontrollera' has more than 6 letters)

There are 9 complex words in the text.

However, to be sure that words really are 'complex', one alternative (used in general science description of use calculating LIX) is to instead manually count the amounts of the longest syllable sequence of a given word; I'm using that as they describe use in original paper introducing and applying in Swedish newspapers way back – (more than 3-4 syllables).

There are 10 words with 3-4 or more syllable.
